<h1 class="off">Scientific Evidence</h1><br>

As we age, we lose natural oils and hydration in the skin, which
causes a change in skin tone, complexion, and firmness. The skin
matrix also changes, making it less elastic over time, which can lead to
wrinkles and sagging skin. Studies have found that after facial
rejuvenation acupuncture treatments the water and
natural oil content of the skin increased  (1), and there was also a significant
improvement in elasticity and collagen formation in skin (2,3).<br>

